Review kali ini cukup panjang dan jujur apa adanya. Rencana hari ini pulang ke jakarta setelah melalui liburan panjang menginap di salah 1 hotel ternyaman di Bandung. Namun dikarenakan jalanan macet parah sekitar jam 10 malam masih dicihampelas, jadi terpaksa harus pesan penginapan. Dan yang lebih parah lagi di laci pantry itu ada banyak kumpulan tisu-tisu bekas. thank jorok banget. Bingung sama managementnya bagaimana cara bersihinnya sih. kok tidak dicek dulu. Saya dan suami cuma bsa berharap semoga malam ini segera berakhir biar besok pagi bisa cepet-cepet pulang. teruntuk manajement penginapan disini, Tolong lah dibikin lebih manusiawi penginapannya. Aya menginap 3 hari 2 malam, hari pertama (11 des 2019 ) saya sewa 4 kamar deluxe di depan pool hanya ada sedikit masalah yaitu sprei dikamar 111 dan 109 kurang bersih tetapi team Housekeeping siap tanggap ketika saya meminta untuk menggantinya. Dihari ke dua (12 des 2019) saya pesan premium villa dengan harga jauh lebih mahal dari tipe villa family suite dan deluxe villa saya memilih tipe premium villa karna saya ingin mendapatkan kenyaman dengan fasilitas lengkap yang diberikan didalam villa tetapi yang saya dapat kan didalam ( bungalow 2 ) hanya 2 kamar twin bed, 1 kamar double bed,1 bathroom dan ruang tamu tanpa ada meja makan dan kulkas sangat jauh berbeda dengan apa yang saya lihat di foto. Ketika saya mengobrol dengan salah satu team housekeeping dan menanyakan mengenai villa premium beliau menunjuk bangunan villa yang terlihat lebih baru dari pada yang saya tempati disitu saya merasa dibohongi oleh front office kenapa memberikan saya dan keluarga villa yang tidak sesuai bukan soal bangunan baru atau lama yang penting adalah mendapatkan fasilitas yang sesuai. Ketika saya check out dan mempertanyakan soal hal ini tanggapan team FO pun sangat mengecewakan tidak seperti perkerja di dunia hospitality salah satu staff (laki2) menanyakan rate harga premiun villa kepada partner kerja nya(perempuan) didepan saya setelah saya bilang kalo saya memilih villa yang harga nya lebih mahal dari villa lainnya lalu si partner ini menjawab bahwa harga premium villa (400rb) mereka saja sbg staff FO tidak tau berapa rate harga yang ada di aplikasi traveloka. Saya benar kecewa dengan team FO! Saya sangat mengapresiasi untuk team housekeeping yang cepat tanggap dan sangat membantu. Untuk sarapan nasgor dan slice fruit enak pengiriman tepat waktu.

Petugasnya ramah-ramah, pintu gerbang walau ditutup tapi bisa akses 24 jam, jadi bagi yang ada acara sampai tengah malam, tidak usah khawatir pintu dikunci. Kamar sih masih lumayan lah, walau pas masuk agak bau apek, mungkin karena sirkulasi udaranya kurang. AC nya juga dingin kok, masukannya, pewanginya kalau bisa diganti rutin agar kamar tetap wangi. Untuk kamar mandi, airnya bersih dan lumayan deras serta tidak sempit juga, hanya banyak sisaan rambut di wastafel, mungkin petugas kebersihannya mesti lebih teliti jika membersihkan kamar mandi nya. Yang paling saya suka, ada kulkasnya, jadi bisa simpan makanan dan minuman siap saji.
The price is cheap, service okay, cleanliness was excellent (just note again the bathroom grooming tools, has begun to rust), which importantly safe.

Good location, right beside Mall at Bassura City so you won't get bored. It is also pretty close to Halim Airport. Pretty close even though we're at the farthest tower. There's swimming pool, 24-hr receptionist. Check in was smooth too! Friendly staff. The aircon is pretty cold. Washroom is combined with the toilet, and it is pretty small (but quite clean). There's locker in the second room with the bunk bed. The downsides are, the apartment looks pretty worn down. While it is quite clean it's very visible that this is an old unit that hasn't been maintained for a while. There are loads of baby cockroaches; some crawled out of the water dispenser, some seemed to have taken residence in the second bed room. I know you're choosing this because it's cheap. Don't bother. When I arrived at the lobby (it was a stall on the ground floor of the apartment) it was closed. They had a number and another office (at another tower) listed that I was supposed to get to to check myself in. I arrived at the very dirty and spooky lobby (the glass cabinet in the picture was just behind the receptionits desk. He checked me in, impatiently telling me that it's the same management as the oyo one, not to fuss too much, and to just go to my room. Pissed, I left for the tower lobby (which I had to ask around for because I wasn't given much directions). The security asked me to leave my ID there (standard procedure, it was fine) but dragged the conversation and asked if I was going to have anyone joining me(i was alone. He had my ID. HE KNEW MY ROOM NUMBER). Started feeling pretty unsafe. I left the desk anyways, took the elevator to the 11th floor, and entered the room 1111. I explored the room for like 2-3 minutes and exited the building to try and find another accommodation nearby. A conversation with the creepy security guard in the lobby (who btw, read my address and tried to talk to me about the area because his friend worked there, all whilst holding onto my ID--had my hand held out for it the whole time) led me to the understanding that I was not actually the first of guest to leave. Once I got my id back, I went to the lobby to return the key. The guy asked why I am checking out. At that I just told him the room was different (I've been out the whole day in bekasi heat doing interviews from home to home. It was 9PM. I just wanted a shower and maybe sleep). To which he answered, "oh well of course. All the rooms are different from the pictures". If you're considering this: save yourself the pain. Go to others instead.
